@iliazeus 

I made commit 14cd6f5 removing the masks and forgot to link here. That fixed this specific issue, but made `keyboard.send('windows')` break (#147). I'm investigating now.

Note that functions like [MapVirtualKeyEx](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms646307(v=vs.85).aspx) use the high-order byte of the returned scan code (which is apparently 0xe000 and not 0xe0000000 as expected from an UINT) to signify extended key ranges, which is now causing trouble when trying to simulate key presses of the windows key.

