@At0mik the timeout in the requests library is not a hard timeout, it is a connect timeout The timeout in the sdk is a "give up" timeout.

The difference is that if you can connect at all, but the rest API hangs, you will never timeout with requests. Likewise, if reads are slow, you will also hang forever.

The sdk enforces a hard timeout so that the script is killed if it exceeds the timeout.

