Thanks for catching this issue.  OpenThread maintains a fragment offset for each child in the child table.  I think a more complete fix would set the message offset based on the child's fragment offset when preparing to transmit.  What do you think about something like:

```c
void MeshForwarder::ScheduleTransmissionTask()
{
    ....
    for (int i = 0; i < numChildren; i++)
    {
     	if (children[i].mState == Child::kStateValid &&
            children[i].mDataRequest &&
            (mSendMessage = GetIndirectTransmission(children[i])) != NULL)
        {
            mSendMessage->SetOffset(children[i].mFragmentOffset);  ///< Set offset here.
            mMac.SendFrameRequest(mMacSender);
            ExitNow();
        }
    }
    ....
}
```

